bei.  aWhat is the role of utopia in the process of European integration? What does the term »Utopian Europe« mean in times of economic and financial crises in the EU? By analyzing its fundamental legal texts, Marcus Koch points out the position of utopian ideas in European unification, and how they have changed through the course of history. Once more, this study shows that utopian ideas are a driving force of political processes, and contributes to the discourse about the attractiveness and sensibility of the now heavily scolded European Union.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aUtopiaszEuropexHistory. 4aEuropa. 4aEuropäische Idee. 4aEuropäische Integration. 4aEuropäische Politik. 4aEuropäische Union. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aPolitische Theorie. 4aUtopische Idee. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aEurope.  aEuropean Idea.  aEuropean Integration.  aEuropean Politics.  aEuropean Union.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.  aUtopian Imagination.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2015 Part 2z978311076664608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z97831107009850 cprintz978383762958340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839429587?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839429587zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839429587/original  a978-3-11-070098-5 DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076664-6 DG Plus PP Package 2015 Part 2b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA